<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE paragraph PUBLIC "-//IFRS//DTD DITA Paragraph//EN" "../../../DocTypes/com.ifrs.doctype/dtd/paragraph.dtd"><paragraph base="F29577487" id="IFRS14_29"><paranum class="- topic/title paragraph/paranum "/><titlealts><navtitle>29</navtitle></titlealts><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 14"/><data name="paranum" value="29"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS14_P0076">To meet the disclosure objective in <xref base="F35710582" href="IFRS14_g27-36.dita#IFRS14_g27-36/IFRS14_g27-36_TI" id="IFRS14_X0132">paragraph 27</xref>, an entity shall consider all of the following:</p><ol outputclass="static" base="F29577489" type="lower-alpha" id="IFRS14_L0007"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p base="F29577490" id="IFRS14_P0077">the level of detail that is necessary to satisfy the disclosure requirements;</p>       </li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p base="F29577492" id="IFRS14_P0078">how much emphasis to place on each of the various requirements;</p>       </li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value>         <p base="F29577521" id="IFRS14_P0079">how much aggregation or disaggregation to undertake; and</p>       </li><li><li_value>(d)</li_value>         <p base="F29577523" id="IFRS14_P0080">whether users                                 of financial statements need additional information to evaluate the quantitative information disclosed.</p>       </li></ol></body></paragraph>